---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHero from '../components/SectionHero.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Visit — Matteo Martignoni"
  description="Brand strategy, investment in innovative startups, Italian residency through the Investor Visa programme."
  lang="en"
>
  <SectionHero
    number="04"
    tagline="Who this is for"
    title="A few good reasons to reach out."
    intro="Three kinds of work. Read to find your context."
  />

  <section class="max-w-2xl mt-12 md:mt-16 space-y-0">

    <!-- 01 · Brand work -->
    <div class="border-t border-warm-200 pt-10 md:pt-12 pb-10 md:pb-12">
      <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-5">
        <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-terracotta-900 tabular-nums shrink-0">01</span>
        <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-500">Brand Directors · CEOs · CMOs</span>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium text-ink-900 mb-5">
        The brand work I know best.
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-2">
        Brand strategy, repositioning, category development, distribution,
        retail performance, European market entry.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Twenty-five years with Diesel, Aēsop, Eastpak, Reflex, and the
        companies I founded. The problems tend to repeat.
        The solutions rarely do.
      </p>
      
        href="mailto:martignoni.matteo@gmail.com"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-terracotta-900 hover:text-terracotta-700 transition-colors duration-200"
      >
        <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        <span>martignoni.matteo@gmail.com</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- 02 · Investors -->
    <div class="border-t border-warm-200 pt-10 md:pt-12 pb-10 md:pb-12">
      <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-5">
        <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-terracotta-900 tabular-nums shrink-0">02</span>
        <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-500">Investors · Business Angels · Funds</span>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium text-ink-900 mb-5">
        Two companies worth a closer look.
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        NOVA is an AI experience company building a proprietary platform
        for museums and cultural institutions. Officina degli Estratti
        develops high-end cosmetic ingredients from certified Parmesan
        animal byproducts, with an AI-driven quality and standardisation
        platform.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Both have structured business plans and a clear path forward.
        Both are registered as Italian innovative startups.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        We are looking for partners who can strengthen our governance,
        not only provide capital. If the work interests you, I am open
        to a conversation.
      </p>
      
        href="mailto:martignoni.matteo@gmail.com"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-terracotta-900 hover:text-terracotta-700 transition-colors duration-200"
      >
        <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        <span>martignoni.matteo@gmail.com</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- 03 · Golden Visa -->
    <div class="border-t border-warm-200 pt-10 md:pt-12 pb-10 md:pb-12">
      <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-5">
        <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-terracotta-900 tabular-nums shrink-0">03</span>
        <span class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-500">Extra-EU Investors</span>
      </div>
      <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium text-ink-900 mb-5">
        Residency through innovation.
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        The Italian government's Investor Visa programme allows
        extra-EU nationals to apply for an Italian residency permit
        through a qualifying investment in an Italian innovative startup.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Both NOVA and Officina degli Estratti are structured to qualify.
        If you are exploring this route, an investment in either company
        could open that path.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        This is not legal or financial advice. The official framework
        and eligibility requirements are governed by the Italian Ministry
        of Enterprise and Made in Italy. The conversation I can offer
        is about the investment itself.
      </p>
      
        href="mailto:martignoni.matteo@gmail.com"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-terracotta-900 hover:text-terracotta-700 transition-colors duration-200"
      >
        <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        <span>martignoni.matteo@gmail.com</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-warm-200" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  </section>

</BaseLayout>
